<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870717-0143 </DOCNO><HL> National Fuel Gas Co. Unit</HL><DD> 07/17/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> CANDA NFGNATURAL GAS, PIPELINES (LNG)ENERGY DEPARTMENT (ERG) </IN><DATELINE> BUFFALO, N.Y.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   National Fuel Gas Co. said its National Fuel Gas Supply Corp. unit received approval from the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission to construct a pipeline to transport Canadian natural gas.    The oil and gas producer said the 12.3-mile, 24-inch pipeline will cost about $12 million and will be constructed in Erie County, N.Y. About 115 miles of existing pipeline also will be upgraded as part of the project.    The company said the pipeline will be used to transport about 90 million cubic feet of natural gas a day from Alberta, Canada. It expects to begin operating the pipeline in November. </TEXT></DOC>